      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/9/1/5/2",
      "text": [
        " الله عزوجل: ” إنما يخشى الله من عباده العلماء ” قال: يعني بالعلماء من صدق فعله قوله، ومن لم يصدق فعله قوله فليس بعالم"
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.ammaar-muslim": [
          "2. [2/24] al-Kafi: Ali b. Ibrahim from Muhammad b. Isa from Yunus from Hammad b. Uthman from al-Harith b. al-Mughira al-Nasri from Abi Abdillah عليه السلام in regards the words of Allāh Mighty and Majestic: “Verily they truly fear Allāh from among his slaves – the scholars” <a href=\"/books/quran:35#h28\">[35:28]</a> he said: He means by the scholars the one whose deeds conform with his words, as for the one whose deeds are contrary to his words then he is not a scholar."
        ]
      }
    },
